The paper discusses a crowd-based system for screening literature reviews, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves text classification and information retrieval, which are relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) respectively. The paper also discusses the use of AI, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
